Q2 A) Write a Python NumPy program to compute the weighted average
along the specified axis of a given flattened array.

import numpy as np
arr = np.array([1, 2, 3, 4, 5])
weights = np.array([1, 2, 3, 4, 5])
avg = np.average(arr, weights=weights)
print('Weighted average of the flattened array:',avg)


B) Write a Python program to view basic statistical details of
 the data (Use advertising.csv)

import pandas as pd
df = pd.read_csv(r'C:\dataset\advertising.csv')
print('Description of the dataset:')
print(df.describe())
